caller_intent: Gary is providing detailed information about his property (roof age, heating system, structures, outbuildings, pets) and auto insurance provider to facilitate an insurance quote or assessment.
resolution_steps: Shane gathers details about the property's metal roof (5-6 years old, installed by Piedmont Metal Roofing), heat pump (5 years old), and wooden carport with telephone poles.
Confirms presence of two outbuildings (Leonard's aluminum and Rhino sheds) in good condition, and pets (two cats, a non-vicious Great Pyrenees dog).
Notes that the mortgage company is Ashcroft, now under Mister Cooper, and that auto insurance is with State Farm.
Informs Gary he will contact him in a few days with rate estimates.
knowledge_required: Home insurance factors (roof age, heating systems, property structures, outbuildings, pets)
Insurance carrier transitions (Mid America to Mister Cooper)
summary: Gary provides comprehensive property and insurance details to Shane during a consultation. Shane confirms key factors affecting insurance coverage and agrees to follow up with rate estimates. The conversation includes details about roof installations, heating systems, outbuildings, and carrier transitions.
